        "# Mathematical Functions and Operations\n",
        "\n",
        "### 1. **Functions and Their Values at \\($ x = 2 $\\)**\n",
        "\n",
        "Given the following functions:\n",
        "\n",
        "- \\($ f(x) = x^2 $\\)\n",
        "- \\($ g(x) = x $\\)\n",
        "- \\($ h(x) = \\frac{1}{x} $\\)\n",
        "- \\($ j(x) = \\sin(x) $\\)\n",
        "\n",
        "Find the value of these functions at \\($ x = 2 $\\).\n",
        "\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "f(2) = 2^2 = 4\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "g(2) = 2\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "h(2) = \\frac{1}{2} = 0.5\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "j(2) = \\sin(2) \\approx 0.909\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\n",
        "### 2. **Composition of Functions**\n",
        "\n",
        "Let:\n",
        "- \\($ f(x) = 3x - 1 $\\)\n",
        "- \\($ g(x) = x $\\)\n",
        "\n",
        "Find the following compositions:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "f(g(x)) = f(x) = 3x - 1\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "g(f(x)) = g(3x - 1) = 3x - 1\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "f(f(x)) = f(3x - 1) = 3(3x - 1) - 1 = 9x - 4\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "g(g(x)) = g(x) = x\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\n",
        "You can visualize these functions in a single Geogebra notebook.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3. **Exponential and Logarithmic Functions**\n",
        "\n",
        "Let:\n",
        "- \\($ f(x) = e^x $\\)\n",
        "- \\($ g(x) = \\ln(x) $\\)\n",
        "\n",
        "Now check the compositions:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "f(g(x)) = e^{\\ln(x)} = x\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "g(f(x)) = \\ln(e^x) = x\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\n",
        "Notice that:\n",
        "- \\($ f(g(x)) = x $\\)\n",
        "- \\($ g(f(x)) = x $\\)\n",
        "\n",
        "These are inverse functions of each other.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 4. **Finding Inverse Function**\n",
        "\n",
        "Given the function \\($ f = \\{(1, 7), (2, 9), (3, 11)\\} $\\), find the inverse function \\($ f^{-1} $\\).\n",
        "\n",
        "To find the inverse function, swap the \\($ x $\\)- and \\($ y $\\)-coordinates:\n",
        "- \\($ f^{-1} = \\{(7, 1), (9, 2), (11, 3)\\} $\\)\n",
        "\n",
        "### 5. **Another Inverse Function**\n",
        "\n",
        "Given the function \\($ f = \\{(1, 7), (2, 7), (3, 11)\\} $\\), find the inverse function \\($ f^{-1} $\\).\n",
        "\n",
        "Note that since \\($ f(1) = f(2) = 7 $\\), this function is not one-to-one, and an inverse function does not exist in the conventional sense.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 6. **Inverse Function of a Linear Function**\n",
        "\n",
        "Given the function \\($ f(x) = x - 1 $\\), find the inverse function \\($ f^{-1} $\\).\n",
        "\n",
        "To find the inverse, swap \\($ x $\\) and \\($ y $\\), then solve for \\($ y $\\):\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "y = x - 1\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "x = y - 1\n",
        "$\\]\n",
        "\\[$\n",
        "f^{-1}(x) = x + 1\n",
        "$\\]"
      ],
